WEBVTT

00:07.091 --> 00:09.457
(J‘ Scale played falteringly on trumpet)

00:24.275 --> 00:26.061
(J‘ Continues to practice scales)

00:26.194 --> 00:28.025
(Approaching footsteps)

00:28.154 --> 00:29.519
(Door opens)

00:30.448 --> 00:32.439
— Robert!
— I gotta practice, Ma.

00:32.575 --> 00:35.237
Take it down the street for a while.
You're working my last nerve.

00:35.369 --> 00:38.111
— I'm not asking you again.
— All right.

00:38.247 --> 00:40.283
(J‘ Continues to practice scales)

00:41.292 --> 00:42.657
(Door slams shut)

00:46.339 --> 00:48.125
(Chickens cluck)

00:54.180 --> 00:55.761
(Church bells toll)

01:00.186 --> 01:02.177
(Match striking)

01:25.419 --> 01:27.910
(J‘ I Thought I Heard Buddy Bolden Say)

01:43.396 --> 01:44.806
(Wings flutter)

01:53.864 --> 01:57.152
— (On radio: J‘ Opera)
— (Entrance bell jangles)

01:59.370 --> 02:02.112
— Lemon ice tastes the same. Better.
- Glad.

02:02.248 --> 02:03.988
Saw the picture in the paper.

02:04.125 --> 02:06.867
Yes, the line goin' back was around the block.

02:11.257 --> 02:13.919
— Everybody missed you.
— We're glad to be back.

02:15.594 --> 02:17.095
(J‘ Continues playing)

02:47.585 --> 02:49.450
This was a good idea, Sof.

02:49.587 --> 02:51.418
(On radio: J‘ Opera)

02:53.841 --> 02:55.627
| wish Daddy were here.

02:58.512 --> 02:59.968
(J‘ Continues playing)

03:16.113 --> 03:17.944
(J‘ Trumpet plays in distance)

03:19.116 --> 03:21.277
(J‘ Continues to practice scales)

03:29.418 --> 03:30.658
(Blows air)

03:34.173 --> 03:36.164
(J‘ Continues to practice scales)

03:38.803 --> 03:40.668
(J‘ Trumpet plays in distance)

03:48.020 --> 03:50.011
(J‘ Trumpet gets louder)

04:01.242 --> 04:03.449
(J‘ Continues to practice scales)

05:50.309 --> 05:52.391
J‘ We'll take a boat

05:52.520 --> 05:54.761
J‘ To the land of dreams

05:54.897 --> 05:58.936
J‘ Roll down the river,
down to New Orleans

05:59.068 --> 06:01.559
J‘ The band's there to meet us

06:03.322 --> 06:06.109
J‘ Friends are there to greet us

06:08.327 --> 06:12.741
J‘ Where all the light and dark folks meet

06:12.873 --> 06:16.866
J‘ Heaven on earth, they call it Basin Street

06:17.002 --> 06:19.709
- J‘ Basin Street... J‘
— (J‘ Band playing Li'l Liza Jane)

06:22.800 --> 06:24.791
Poseurs!

06:27.638 --> 06:29.469
J‘ Basin Street

06:30.558 --> 06:32.139
J‘ That's the street... J‘

06:32.268 --> 06:33.849
(Car horns honking)

06:34.937 --> 06:37.349
(Woman) Picking up!
Tasting menu for three.

06:37.481 --> 06:41.065
— OK, we're firing. Two scallop.
— Two scallop.

06:41.193 --> 06:42.308
- One ravioli.
— (Man) Ravi.

06:42.444 --> 06:44.526
- One pigeon and a duck.
— (Man) One pigeon, one duck.

06:44.655 --> 06:47.317
— Next coming in — three market salads.
— (Man) Three salads.

06:47.449 --> 06:48.609
— Two tuna tartares.
- (Man) Two tunas.

06:48.742 --> 06:50.778
- Two cod, one snapper.
— (Man) Two cod, one snapper.

06:50.911 --> 06:53.243
(Woman) All right, watch yourself...

06:53.372 --> 06:55.158
Young man.

06:55.291 --> 06:56.747
— Young man!
- Sir?

06:56.875 --> 06:58.126
Yes, you.

06:59.336 --> 07:01.713
Lobsters. Get me some lobsters.

07:01.839 --> 07:05.172
Fuck me, no way.
He's not serious.

07:05.301 --> 07:07.087
Yes, he is. And the best part is...

07:07.219 --> 07:08.834
we got no fucking lobster.

07:08.971 --> 07:11.383
He's gotta send that kid
to fucking Chinatown to get some.

07:11.515 --> 07:12.846
Twelve one—and—a—half pounders.

07:12.975 --> 07:14.886
— Get me a receipt, and hurry the fuck up.
— Right away, Chef.

07:15.019 --> 07:17.385
No sleepers. Make sure they're happy.
I want peppy lobsters.

07:17.521 --> 07:19.386
— Yes, Chef.
- Peppy.

07:19.523 --> 07:20.387
Menu change.

07:20.524 --> 07:25.518
We're doing butter—poached lobster
with roasted corn coulis...

07:25.654 --> 07:28.111
and something to be determined later.

07:28.240 --> 07:29.446
Right now, Entremetier!

07:29.575 --> 07:31.907
— Roast me some fucking corn!
— Yes, Chef.

07:32.036 --> 07:36.029
Oh my God, he gives that to us,
I'm gonna go in the walk—in and cry. Fuck.

07:36.165 --> 07:38.907
Degustation's got what?
We have... (Sighs)

07:39.043 --> 07:42.535
..the razor clams, the salmon, the cod.
Now he's gonna squeeze in fucking lobster?

07:42.671 --> 07:45.083
Why not just shove
a goddamn pineapple up my ass?

07:45.215 --> 07:47.080
He's giving it to the saucier.

07:47.217 --> 07:50.425
The chefs been looking at her funny all night.
You know the look?

07:50.554 --> 07:53.216
Yeah, I've seen it.
In my fucking nightmares I've seen it.

07:53.349 --> 07:55.089
That's why I try not to look at the guy.

07:55.225 --> 07:58.717
Never directly, right?
'Cause the eyes is like his way in.

07:58.854 --> 08:02.187
That's how he gets you.
That's how he gets inside — he looks at you.

08:02.316 --> 08:04.307
Then he crawls up in your brain...

08:04.443 --> 08:06.525
takes a big dump on it...

08:06.654 --> 08:08.144
and then he's got you.

08:08.280 --> 08:11.943
— "Avoid the eyes" is what you're saying.
— Yeah, avoid the fucking eyes.

08:12.076 --> 08:15.614
(Chef) Madame le saucier!
(Man) It's looking good, it's looking great.

08:15.746 --> 08:18.078
— (Sighs) Yes, Chef.
- Ah.

08:18.207 --> 08:21.244
You'll be doing the lobster course.
Get your station ready.

08:21.377 --> 08:22.492
Absolutely, Chef.

08:22.628 --> 08:25.540
Coming down the line! Behind.

08:26.965 --> 08:30.674
(Man) Can you take that off the heat for me?
(Man 2) Right away, Chef.

08:40.729 --> 08:41.764
(Crowd cheering)

08:41.897 --> 08:46.266
J‘ Oh, I once had a vision
J‘ Ooh—ooh—ooh ooh—ooh ooh

08:46.402 --> 08:51.066
J‘ Like an old—time love story
J‘ Ooh ooh ooh

08:51.198 --> 08:54.656
J‘ I want to whisper in your ear

08:54.785 --> 08:55.991
J‘ Ooh—ooh

08:56.120 --> 09:00.705
J‘ Watch the light in your eyes

09:04.628 --> 09:06.914
J‘ Light in your eyes J‘

09:33.741 --> 09:35.857
(Applause, cheering)

09:39.329 --> 09:43.868
There you go! Annie Tee on the fiddle!
Annie Tee on the fiddle.

09:44.001 --> 09:45.457
- (Applause)
— (Man) Love you, Annie!

09:45.586 --> 09:48.248
(Lead singer) Yes, indeed.
(Man) All right!

09:48.380 --> 09:51.543
Back home it was All Saints' Day.
Y'all might not know that.

09:51.675 --> 09:54.917
— They do All Saints' Day here in Connecticut?
— (Man) Whoo!

09:55.053 --> 09:56.463
How about All Souls' Day?

09:57.389 --> 09:59.095
Don't know it, huh?

09:59.224 --> 10:01.180
Well, in New Orleans
it's a pretty big deal,

10:01.310 --> 10:04.097
so we're gonna do this song
right here for you, all right?

10:06.064 --> 10:08.100
J‘ Carved in stone

10:09.109 --> 10:10.565
J‘ Is a name

10:10.694 --> 10:13.231
J‘ I will remember

10:14.948 --> 10:16.484
Yeah, baby.

10:16.617 --> 10:18.983
J‘ Skin and bone

10:19.119 --> 10:20.655
J‘ And the heart

10:20.788 --> 10:23.780
J‘ That was so tender... J‘

10:24.500 --> 10:26.832
(On radio:
J‘ 10th Ward Buck: Drop & Gimme 50)

10:28.170 --> 10:30.832
Sofia B. Real here from New Orleans.

10:30.964 --> 10:33.501
Y'all may have forgotten about us,
but we're still here.

10:33.634 --> 10:35.875
Can we talk about the so—called recovery?

10:36.011 --> 10:38.593
lt sucks...the big one.

10:38.722 --> 10:41.384
Fourteen months,
and it ought to be getting better here.

10:41.517 --> 10:44.008
Fourteen months,
and it ought to be getting easier.

10:44.144 --> 10:46.726
It ought to be getting fixed. You feel me?

10:46.855 --> 10:48.561
Well, it isn't.

10:48.690 --> 10:50.430
It gets harder every day.

10:51.527 --> 10:55.236
There's still 100,000 empty houses
in New Orleans, at least.

10:55.364 --> 10:57.730
100,000 families that can't get home.

10:57.866 --> 11:01.609
Everyone in this frickin' city
is on painkillers or booze.

11:02.371 --> 11:05.989
No kidding,
85% of the city is doped just to cope.

11:06.124 --> 11:08.786
And you need an AK—47 to go out at night.

11:08.919 --> 11:13.162
And the frickin' National Guard
is patrolling our streets like...

11:13.298 --> 11:15.550
we're Fallujah or something.

11:16.844 --> 11:18.254
So you know what?

11:19.304 --> 11:22.137
Drop and give me 50, you fucking fucks.

11:23.183 --> 11:24.593
(Turns up radio)

11:32.776 --> 11:34.107
(Turns down music)

11:34.236 --> 11:39.572
That was 10th Ward Buck with his timeless
standard, the evergreen Drop & Gimme 50.

11:39.700 --> 11:43.659
Oh, must be time
for the OZ Live Music Calendar.

11:43.787 --> 11:45.118
I'll be right back.

11:46.582 --> 11:48.447
— Davis.
— Darnell.

11:48.584 --> 11:50.996
— I thought you left hours ago.
— I heard the show and came back.

11:51.128 --> 11:52.709
— Mix it up a little, will you?
— Absolutely.

11:52.838 --> 11:55.329
- I'm serious.
— So am |. Look at my face.

11:57.009 --> 11:59.091
I got Gin In My System.

11:59.219 --> 12:01.961
I thought that was a Coke!
And don't spill it in the control board.

12:02.097 --> 12:04.088
— You will pay for this one.
— Empty threat.

12:04.224 --> 12:07.341
Then you'd have me around
for the next 20 years, working it off.

12:07.477 --> 12:09.638
I got Gin In My System on deck.

12:10.689 --> 12:13.681
Big Freedia. A little tranny bounce
as a change of pace.

12:13.817 --> 12:15.603
That's not what I mean by mixing it up.

12:15.736 --> 12:19.024
Brass band, funk, trad jazz, rock 'n' roll...

12:19.156 --> 12:20.646
- I don't care.
— Oh! I feel you.

12:20.782 --> 12:23.740
How about a little acoustic Piedmont blues
from Bumble Bee Slim?

12:23.869 --> 12:25.905
A little lullaby
to put our audience to sleep?

12:26.038 --> 12:29.280
You know what?
I don't even mind you playing a little...bounce.

12:29.416 --> 12:31.532
Once in a while. Just not nonstop.

12:32.294 --> 12:34.250
Mix it up, Davis.

12:36.548 --> 12:37.924
(Sighs)

12:40.844 --> 12:43.836
So go out and see some live local music.

12:43.972 --> 12:46.054
Oh, and bring your gun.

12:46.183 --> 12:49.846
Uh, this one goes out to someone who,
at the moment,

12:49.978 --> 12:53.186
is very much on my mind.

12:54.691 --> 12:56.898
J‘ Carry on

12:58.111 --> 13:00.227
J‘ Have yourself

13:00.364 --> 13:02.946
J‘ A lovely ride

13:05.077 --> 13:07.033
J‘ Think of me

13:07.829 --> 13:10.286
J‘ When you finally

13:10.415 --> 13:12.872
J‘ Reach the other side

13:22.594 --> 13:24.050
(Woman) Yeah!

13:55.460 --> 13:56.666
(Cheering and applause)

13:56.795 --> 13:58.501
J‘ Hold on tight

13:59.631 --> 14:01.371
J‘ To the things

14:02.259 --> 14:04.841
J‘ You always taught us... J‘

14:06.847 --> 14:07.802
(J‘ Hip—hop)

14:07.931 --> 14:09.887
— (Man) It's more of a white thing.
— You think?

14:10.017 --> 14:12.429
Dressing up and shit? Oh, yeah.

14:13.353 --> 14:15.810
— They got Halloween in Holland, right?
- No.

14:15.939 --> 14:17.520
They don't? Shit.

14:18.442 --> 14:19.557
They got Mardi Gras though?

14:19.693 --> 14:20.853
- 7 and 7?
— Yeah, man.

14:20.986 --> 14:24.319
- That's a Catholic thing.
— So what, y'all ain't Catholic?

14:24.448 --> 14:26.609
Not so much. We got Queen's Day.

14:26.742 --> 14:28.448
Everybody wears orange.

14:28.577 --> 14:30.784
Sounds like Hallo—fucking—ween to me.

14:31.872 --> 14:33.783
(Gunshots, people screaming)

14:39.463 --> 14:40.748
(Woman groans)

14:43.592 --> 14:46.334
— (Woman groans)
— (Tires screech)

14:48.722 --> 14:51.134
Five.
We expect the four wounded to recover.

14:51.266 --> 14:55.009
Sorry to disappoint you —
I know "five dead" would make a better story.

14:55.145 --> 14:57.101
This is all off—the—record, right?

14:57.230 --> 15:00.893
You want an official statement,
you need to call the PIO.

15:01.026 --> 15:02.357
Leads?

15:05.030 --> 15:06.440
No, no leads.

15:07.991 --> 15:10.573
One or two.
We're still sorting that out.

15:11.286 --> 15:14.403
No, things were worse last spring
and this summer.

15:14.539 --> 15:17.281
I'm sure it is having an impact on tourism.

15:18.543 --> 15:23.082
That piece of mayhem didn't have anything
to do with Katrina. He was a vet. Iraq.

15:24.091 --> 15:27.254
Listen...
Listen, | read the note.

15:27.385 --> 15:29.091
I went to the scene.

15:29.221 --> 15:31.428
Stuff like that can happen anywhere.

15:33.141 --> 15:35.097
The stove and the refrigerator.

15:35.227 --> 15:39.561
Yeah, but he didn't eat her.
Not like that guy in the East Village years ago.

15:39.689 --> 15:41.225
Uh—huh, look it up.

15:41.358 --> 15:43.519
You'll mention that in your article?

15:44.486 --> 15:46.272
You're welcome.

15:46.404 --> 15:51.114
Jesus. New York Times. I think they live
for the latest grotesquerie from New Orleans.

15:51.243 --> 15:54.030
They just love them some Zack and Addie.
What've you got?

15:54.162 --> 15:57.199
Couple of knuckleheads walk in a club,
see another couple of knuckleheads,

15:57.332 --> 16:00.540
— go to the car, get their guns.
— Bring their neighborhood shit down here.

16:00.669 --> 16:02.625
My phone's ringing off the fucking hook.

16:02.754 --> 16:05.837
Shooting in the Quarter
gets everybody's attention.

16:05.966 --> 16:07.126
Got mine.

16:09.511 --> 16:11.502
Good to go.

16:11.638 --> 16:13.469
— How's business?
— Booming.

16:13.598 --> 16:15.759
— Really?
— More work than we can handle.

16:16.643 --> 16:17.974
Impressive.

16:21.523 --> 16:23.309
(Distant sirens wailing)

16:25.861 --> 16:27.101
(Man) Yeah, so...

16:27.237 --> 16:28.522
So I guess I'll...

16:30.073 --> 16:31.734
I'll see you around?

16:31.867 --> 16:32.982
(Chuckles) Who knows?

16:33.118 --> 16:35.404
— (Janette) Have a good one, OK?
— OK.

16:37.038 --> 16:38.369
— Bye.
— Bye.

16:38.498 --> 16:39.908
(Neighbors yelling)

16:43.378 --> 16:45.084
Go ahead. You can say it.

16:45.797 --> 16:49.836
Hey, no comment implied or intended.
Far from it for l to be judgmental and shit.

16:49.968 --> 16:53.131
— Oh, really? So what?
— I don't know.

16:53.263 --> 16:56.426
You know. First rule, right?

16:57.350 --> 17:00.808
- Don't fuck the floor.
— Hey, he's not my floor.

17:00.937 --> 17:02.552
That's not my restaurant.

17:03.523 --> 17:05.263
I got takeout on the way home.

17:06.109 --> 17:07.394
Is that OK?

17:07.527 --> 17:09.563
My apologies for ever doubting you.

17:10.614 --> 17:12.696
- Wake and bake?
— I gotta go to work.

17:12.824 --> 17:15.031
I guess you kinda need your brain
where you work.

17:15.160 --> 17:18.527
— "Stay alert, stay alive" kind of a thing.
— You guys work stoned where you are?

17:18.663 --> 17:21.370
No, not really.
It's just we don't have to be in till two.

17:24.753 --> 17:25.993
(Coughs)

17:26.129 --> 17:30.122
Oh, man! lwould not want
to be fucked—up at all around Brulard.

17:30.258 --> 17:33.295
Yeah, that dude senses fear —
or at least that's what I hear.

17:33.428 --> 17:36.215
And then he fucks with you
just to prove that he can fuck with you,

17:36.348 --> 17:38.179
because he likes it.

17:38.308 --> 17:39.798
Because he loves it.

17:39.935 --> 17:41.766
— Good cook though, right?
- Oh, he's a great cook.

17:41.895 --> 17:43.726
- Mm.
— Right?

17:45.148 --> 17:48.015
(Car horns honking, people chattering)

17:48.610 --> 17:51.147
(Man) I'm on Carroll Street now.

17:51.279 --> 17:53.656
(Man) Yeah. All right.

17:58.119 --> 17:59.700
(Quiet chatter)

18:12.008 --> 18:13.873
(Man) Do the count.

18:14.010 --> 18:15.125
Hey.

18:16.346 --> 18:18.507
— Hey.
— Hey.

18:20.267 --> 18:21.803
So are we good?

18:21.935 --> 18:23.471
Yeah, we're good.

18:25.522 --> 18:27.103
— Come again.
— Thanks, man.

18:27.232 --> 18:29.063
Tell your friends, will you?

18:30.068 --> 18:31.933
What the fuck was that?

18:32.070 --> 18:33.776
He's cool. We know him.

18:33.905 --> 18:35.861
Yeah, still.

18:37.200 --> 18:38.906
Need an eye opener?

18:40.078 --> 18:41.784
— (Hammers banging)
— Hey, Riley!

18:41.913 --> 18:46.327
— Meet my cousin Nelson, in from Dallas.
- (Men chatting in Spanish)

18:51.047 --> 18:52.958
- Thad Riley.
— Nelson Hidalgo.

18:53.091 --> 18:55.252
You? Related to him?

18:55.385 --> 18:56.750
Oh, by marriage.

18:56.886 --> 18:58.296
(Speaks Spanish)

18:59.973 --> 19:01.929
(Riley and Hidalgo laugh)

19:02.058 --> 19:05.471
Your Spanish is terrible, cuz.
I can't understand a word.

19:06.479 --> 19:08.856
— How long are you here for?
— I'll see how it goes.

19:08.982 --> 19:10.518
Welcome to New Orleans.

19:10.650 --> 19:12.356
I'm liking it so far.

19:16.906 --> 19:20.319
(Car approaches, stops)

19:29.669 --> 19:32.081
Jesus Christ, Albert.

19:35.967 --> 19:37.377
'Fuck's my sign?

19:40.138 --> 19:41.969
(Distant dog barking)

19:43.850 --> 19:45.260
(Sighs)

20:05.914 --> 20:07.950
I can see why your mama
couldn't bear coming back.

20:08.083 --> 20:10.119
Once was all she could handle.

20:11.252 --> 20:14.335
Looka here.
Mama musta put 'em up there and forgot 'em.

20:16.257 --> 20:17.588
Kinda wrinkly.

20:18.593 --> 20:20.584
Oh, they didn't take no water.

20:21.471 --> 20:24.338
Not bad for being in this house
for more than a year.

20:24.474 --> 20:26.010
Phew!

20:27.060 --> 20:29.927
(Antoine)
I guess your mama doing the right thing.

20:30.063 --> 20:32.224
(Desiree) At least she'll get something for it.

20:32.357 --> 20:34.143
(Antoine) Seems a shame though.

20:34.275 --> 20:36.561
You grew up in this house.
She grew up in this house.

20:36.694 --> 20:39.481
What little we get from Road Home...
Can't fix it. Can't afford to.

20:39.614 --> 20:43.232
Hm. I guess.
How soon will she get the money?

20:43.368 --> 20:46.280
They're saying four to six weeks after you file,
they tell you how much.

20:46.413 --> 20:49.621
— I gotta get through the paperwork first.
— You're good at that though.

20:49.749 --> 20:51.990
— They want a deed.
- Oh, shit.

20:53.294 --> 20:55.785
Don't know how the fuck
I'm gonna get around that.

20:55.922 --> 20:59.335
Grandma got it from her Aunt Celeste,
whose daddy built it himself,

20:59.467 --> 21:01.549
who won the land playing bid whist.

21:01.678 --> 21:03.339
It's just always been in our family.

21:03.471 --> 21:06.383
— We taking the bus or you gonna call a cab?
- (Tuts)

21:07.559 --> 21:10.266
I ain't walking all the way over
to no Saint Claude to wait on no bus.

21:10.395 --> 21:14.513
- I'm calling. I'm calling.
— You need to get a job—job, Antoine.

21:14.649 --> 21:17.607
Listen, I know, I know. Ajob—job.

21:17.735 --> 21:21.023
Maybe we could move
into the Musicians' Village.

21:21.156 --> 21:24.444
You really want to move all the
way down here in the ninth ward?

21:25.785 --> 21:28.276
Maybe. It's closer for you though.

21:28.413 --> 21:30.449
We'd have to qualify for a mortgage.

21:30.582 --> 21:32.914
Might have to get married.

21:34.502 --> 21:36.788
— Shit.
— Shit, too.

21:37.839 --> 21:41.377
Oh, here it is.
We're always suing the city.

21:41.509 --> 21:43.795
I am anyhow — one thing or another.

21:43.928 --> 21:48.592
So, after the shootings
